The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 30 March is 260,390 (30,011.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 25 March, there were 8,938 new confirmed cases (1,030.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 18 March, there were 9,932 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 10% (994 fewer cases).
